<br>
IE- Its the plane of Torment, it's supposed to be sheer torture to be in that zone. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=312743" target="top">Sage Cimbaeth</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> 65th Arcanist  of Tunare <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.orderofthephoenix.com" target="top">Order Of The Phoenix</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=claudshadowflare>ClaudShadowflare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Has Eddie Murphy's<BR>taste in women</span><br>  Posts: 3839<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/27/03 4:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Torment</span><hr size=1> Whoever designed that zone should be punched in the face.  Although they at least added loot- even if it's mediocre- to the tower minis.  Losing half your raid to a mob that's swinging around 4000 point hits to recieve a key (worthless after the first time you've cleared to the top) and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>maybe</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> an etheral parchment just plain pisses you off.<br>
<br>
Back when we used to do Saryrn, people kept going AFK, getting left behind, dying, and just having a rogue drag them back up.  The tower climb to Saryrn is quite possibly the 2nd most boring task ever implemented in EQ.  You fight the same exact model 20 or so times, move 50 feet, kill 20 more of the same critters, and repeat that for 3 hours.<br>
<br>
That, and the xp is, was, and I hope won't always be, ass. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quineloe>Quineloe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1992<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/27/03 4:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Torment</span><hr size=1> The problem with Torment is that the zone is Tier2, but unlike the other Tier2 zones the mobs in here are high 50s and rarely range into 60-61. That means no highlevel exp bonus for 65, and since you needed to kill Bertox or TT to enter, you usually were 65 anyways. So Torment looks cool and nice, but since the exp would be good for a low 60 group, it sucks for 65. Torment probably benefits from Plane opening though now that lower people can try it here <p>Sage Quineloe<br>
Arcanist<br>
Venril Sathir</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=absolutemaster>Absolute Master</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 302<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/27/03 6:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Torment</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The tower climb to Saryrn is quite possibly the 2nd most boring task ever implemented in EQ<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
